---
import DocsLayout from "../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import { Code } from "astro-expressive-code/components";---

<DocsLayout title="GDPR Operations">
  <h1>GDPR Operations</h1>
  <p>
    EntDB ships with first-class GDPR primitives on the Python SDK. Every
    operation is routed through the WAL, so each one is captured in the
    compliance audit trail.
  </p>

  <h2>user_id vs tenant_principal</h2>
  <p>
    GDPR operations are scoped by the <strong>global</strong>
    <code>user_id</code> (e.g. <code>"alice"</code>), not by the
    tenant-scoped <code>tenant_principal</code> (e.g.
    <code>"user:alice"</code>). A single user may exist as a principal
    across many tenants, and GDPR rights apply across all of them at once.
  </p>

  <h2>delete_user</h2>
  <p>
    Schedules a user for deletion with a configurable grace window. During
    the grace window the delete is reversible; after the window, all of the
    user's data across every tenant is hard-deleted.
  </p>
  <Code code={`await db.delete_user("alice", grace_period_days=30, reason="user request")`} lang="python" />

  <h2>cancel_user_deletion</h2>
  <p>Cancels a pending deletion during the grace window.</p>
  <Code code={`await db.cancel_user_deletion("alice")`} lang="python" />

  <h2>export_user_data</h2>
  <p>
    Returns every node owned by the user, every ACL entry granted to them,
    and their membership in every tenant. Use this to satisfy the right of
    access and right of portability.
  </p>
  <Code code={`export = await db.export_user_data("alice")
# export.tenants, export.owned_nodes, export.shared_with_me, export.group_memberships`} lang="python" />

  <h2>freeze_user</h2>
  <p>
    Suspends a user without deleting their data. All writes by or to the
    user are rejected; reads of existing data still work. Useful for legal
    hold or account suspension.
  </p>
  <Code code={`await db.freeze_user("alice", reason="legal hold")
await db.unfreeze_user("alice")`} lang="python" />

  <h2>Audit Trail</h2>
  <p>
    Each of these operations appends an event to the WAL with the actor who
    initiated it, the reason string, and the timestamp. When the WAL is
    backed by S3 with Object Lock, the record is tamper-evident.
  </p>
  <p>
    See <a href="/tenant-shard-db/docs/compliance/audit">Compliance &amp; Audit</a>
    for details on Object Lock, crypto-shred, and exporting the audit trail.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
